    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.2.3-4_0001" />
                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                    <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>

                                                                <fw type="letterhead">
                                                                           <hi rend="caps">SYLVANIA
                                                                               <lb/>
                                                                     BARRYTOWN-ON-HUDSON</hi>
                                                                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 1: 1911</dateline>
               
               
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                   <p>Well, I am just delighted to get your note; &amp; I thank you for writing it.</p>
                
                   <p>My books are not the sort that get the most popular applause in this particular age. <del/><add>I</add> often long to transfer them to some other age &amp; see if they wouldn't
                       
                       <pb facs="nei.j4a.2.3-4_0002"/>
                       <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                                      
                       go better.</p>
                
                   <p>With all the philosophy in the world there remains sometimes a doubt as to whether <unclear>one hasn't</unclear> really <unclear>failed</unclear> in the true sense of failure <unclear>&amp;</unclear> written what really <unclear>isn't</unclear> especially valuable anyway &#8212; and perhaps <add>is</add> <unclear>never</unclear> to be discovered at all. I confess your letter <unclear>gives</unclear> me <unclear>infinite</unclear> pleasure.</p>
               <closer>
                                                               <salute>Yours kindly &amp; gratefully</salute>
               
                                                                       <signed>John Jay Chapman</signed>
               </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
